critique: This document pertains to military readiness and the enlistment process for the Ready Reserve components of the armed forces. It authorizes the acceptance of enlistments to maintain the necessary strength for national defense. It does not directly address ideological issues, immigration, or civil liberties. The order delegates regulatory authority to the Secretary of Defense. The document itself doesn't directly expand executive power but rather executes existing legislative authority. It has no implications for federalism, economic regulation, or social inclusion. Therefore, most axes should be scored as neutral.
